# Action goal: move the arm end-effector to a target pose.
#
# target_pose   Desired end-effector pose. The frame_id in the header
#               selects the reference frame (typically the robot base or
#               a chassis-relative frame). Stamp is used for staleness
#               checks; a goal older than the action server's freshness
#               threshold is rejected.

geometry_msgs/PoseStamped target_pose
---
# Action result.
#
# succeeded   True if the arm reached the goal within tolerance, false
#             otherwise. The fortis_arm scaffold returns false with
#             message="kinematics not implemented" until the IK and
#             trajectory pipeline lands.
# message     Human-readable explanation. Always populated.

bool succeeded
string message
---
# Action feedback. Published periodically while the goal is active.
#
# progress    Estimated fraction of the trajectory completed, in
#             [0.0, 1.0]. The scaffold does not publish feedback.

float32 progress
